doc.after: The effective military and bureaucratic structures of the previous century came under strain during a protracted period of misrule by weak Sultans The Ottomans gradually fell behind the Europeans in military technology as the innovation that fed the Empire s forceful expansion became stifled by growing religious and intellectual conservatism 45 But in spite of these difficulties the Empire remained a major expansionist power until the Battle of Vienna in 1683 which marked the end of Ottoman expansion into Europe
